<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-27T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-27T04:00:00-05:00" n="271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/857</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-27T11:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1100. I learn that the Vatican having expressed to Central Empires’
                                Governments surprise that recent replies omitted reference to points
                                in Pope’s letter regarding restoration of Belgium and occupied
                                French territory received yesterday evening reply saying that
                                Germany stands on Reichstag resolutions.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>